@node Features

	OK, here is the big list:

- Fast
- Smart looking GUI (?)
- Can save the list of factors to a file
- Informs if a number is prime
- Informs if a number is a square number

@endnode

@node needs "Requirements"

- OS 2.04 or above (I think)

- @{"MUI" link mui} (I use 3.6, dunno what version my prog needs) for the GUI - @{b}IT
  WILL STILL WORK WITHOUT MUI@{ub}, you just wont have a nice GUI :(

- Some numbers ;)


Tested on:

My Amiga 1200 with Blizzard 030iv (50MHz) board, 16 meg fast
Softkicked OS 3.1 (40.68)
MUI 3.6

@endnode

@node mui "Why MUI?"

I chose to program the GUI in MUI as this is the first GUI I've made, and I'd heard MUI was easy - if this is easy I don't want to see difficult!
Anyway, on my machine its not slow :)
@endnode

@node notes "Notes"

   The largest number you can input and get results for is 2147483647 (2^31 - 1)
   (if you need bigger... tell me how to do it???)

@endnode

@node bugs "BUGS!!!"

